      'Some shops offer 100 kg or 200 kg MOQs. The work is the same — same plates, same setup, same waste — so the per-piece cost is meaningfully higher. We have seen 100 kg quotes from other shops that work out to 60-80% per-piece price premium over a 300 kg run.',
      'In practice, brands that opt for sub-300 kg MOQ usually regret it — either the launch under-sells the plates they paid for, or the per-pouch cost is too high to retail competitively. Our recommendation: order 300 kg of one SKU rather than 100 kg of three SKUs. Validate the brand, then scale.',
